         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">St. Andrew's College, Sandhurst ¶ 23/2/84 ¶ Dear Sir ¶  ¶ Many thanks for the list of names so soon sent me ¶  — a return I did not look for, owing to state of your health, though I know your very gre...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">84.02.23</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Robert Thom</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M73, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS found with a specimen of Compositae (MEL 1547330). MS annotation by M: 'Answ 28/2/84'. Letter not found.</p>
               </note>St. Andrew's College, Sandhurst<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Now Bendigo, Vic.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">23/2/84</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Many thanks for the list of names so soon sent me<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">List not found.</p>
               </note> — a return I did not look for, owing to state of your health, though I know your very great kindness. I hope that the bronchial attack from which you have suffered so much is passing away, it is often very slow to go — my father suffered three years from bronchitis during which time he could not go out after sundown, but he is now well.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I enclose a list of flowers sent me from between Menindie &amp; Wilcannia.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Both on the Darling River in western NSW.</p>
               </note> Unfortunately I was not told which specimens (if any) were got in the Horse paddock where they may have been introduced from Victoria in horse feed or in grass seed. Several of them are common all over South Riverina<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">NSW.</p>
               </note> &amp; Victoria (I think). No. 42 does not belong to the Darling lot — but comes from Sydney or Portarlington<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Vic.</p>
               </note> I forget which (but I think the former). 43 is broken &amp; a poor specimen — so unfortunately is 44 which I dont remember to have seen before.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>My friend tells me that this year has been a very bad one — the long &amp; excessive drought having told severely on all herbage &amp; made it scarce.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With kindest regards</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sincerely yours</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>R Thom</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
